texts.value: Plasmanylethanolamine desaturase involved in plasmalogen biogenesis in the endoplasmic reticulum membrane (PubMed:31604315, PubMed:32209662, PubMed:33859415). Plasmalogens are glycerophospholipids with a hydrocarbon chain linked by a vinyl ether bond at the glycerol sn-1 position, and are involved in antioxidative and signaling mechanisms (PubMed:31604315)
